{italic}Editor Replies:{p}
Regards the first two, we DO have someone workoing on the GUI but he,
like a good number of our editors, also happens to be busy with
college work and other projects as well.  Work IS being done
though.{p}
Regards the next two, one of our editors has been having a rather busy
time of it (school, job, computer problems), and another needs
replacing (care to be our Games Editor?).  Slow output from the Mother
Company doesn't help much either.  Just a couple of slow months is
all.{p}
As for the last point, the article in question was a bit of a rush job
and we were unable to be as thorough in checking anything out.  When
information comes directly from the guy behind a given project you
tend to take their word for the veracity of the links (maybe we
typed one in wrong?  Or the site was temporarily unavailable?).{p}
On the other hand, if {bold}you{nobold} have any suggestions or ideas
for an article then be all means write in or submit something.  We
thrive from input ("Need more input"- quick, name that film).{p}
